Description: IncSpring is an open online marketplace for buying and selling brand logos and domains.
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: IncSpring rebranded to [Brandstack](http://www.crunchbase.com/organization/brandstack). IncSpring provides an open marketplace for high quality, corporate brands. As the first portal for buying and selling complete brands, IncSpring is a way for entrepreneurs and small businesses to reach the best graphic designers in the world. For entrepreneurs, IncSpring can be an extraordinary resource when looking for a unique, well placed brand.  Buyers are able to dip into the portfolios of established designers to see preconceived brands and ideas that would not otherwise be available. The site's rating and feedback features allow buyers to gauge the market's reaction to a brand before it is purchase, essentially eliminating the need for extensive market research.  Businesses will know how a logo or brand name is perceived before ever spending a dime. For designers, IncSpring offers a new and inexpensive way to sell their work to a market that was not previously accessible. Graphic designers never stop creating and are always finding inspiration in everyday life. Their gift not only allows them to create logos for a specific name or industry, but it allows them to develop exciting new brands for businesses to be.  IncSpring matches these ideas with capable entrepreneurs that can carry the theme to fruition. IncSpring also allows designers to sell unused concepts from previous relationships. In a standard custom logo arrangement, designers will develop an average of six concepts for the business owner.  Even if all six concepts are original and flawlessly executed, only one will be used.  That means five creative logos will be stored away, usually not seen again. IncSpring gives you the opportunity to adopt these brands, evolving them into recognizable corporate identities known world wide.
Industry Groups: Advertising, Commerce and Shopping, Financial Services, Information Technology, Privacy and Security, Sales and Marketing

Description: Shared Basket is a Social grocery shopping platform. It reduces the time spent on grocery shopping by making your friends shop for you.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Shared Basket is POOLED GROCERY SHOPPING. 1. Make group of friends. 2. Everybody should make their Grocery Shopping List. 3. Discuss your Grocery Shopping items with your friends. Because you might be purchasing it from somewhere else and your friend from somewhere else. 4. With discussion you will find that many of your items are matching. i.e. you buys from same stores. 5. You are purchasing most (nearly 70%) of the groceries from one store which might be on a distance and rest of the items you are purchasing in every 3–4 days. 6. Now by this you you get many additional advantages like:       1. Get to know how many different stores are there.       2. Get to know the different brands together with their prices.       3. Get to know in which section which store marks up and in which section currently SALE is going on.       4. Get to know what others are purchasing and where they are saving.       5. You can do combine shopping in BULK.       6. You can share your excess groceries or borrow theirs.       7. You get organized.       8. You will be way more updated about groceries.       9. You won’t have to stand in lines every week.     10. You will save your GAS going again and again to different stores.     11. The best part is “You will save TIME, MONEY, ENERGY” 7. Now, for these remaining 30% groceries i.e. 4-5 or 8-10 items every 3–4 days you can ask your friends to bring stuffs for you together with their groceries. And while doing your monthly grocery shopping you can bring few things for your friends as well.  BONUS: - This way you will be maintaining Social Distancing as well. This makes Grocery delivery absolutely free for you. We take privacy very seriously, which is why Shared Basket has the privacy measures to let you hide or show list items to friends, keeping it completely secure. Shared Basket currently has product catalogs from Costco, Walmart, Target, Safeway, Indian Grocery stores, 99 Ranch market, Sprouts farmers market and Whole Foods for the user to choose from. Many more stores to come. We have a built-in, AI based Amart Wallet for your receipts and coupons. Smart Wallet lets users resolve conflicts on the prices they pay for the items. For clear communication between group members, we've also built a chat functionality within the app (similar to WhatsApp). All, the balances are maintained within Shared Basket and the users get an option to settle up balances with others (like Splitswise)

Description: Yakukon is an online dating site/app matches people based on their expectations about married life.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Unlike traditional dating sites that try to match people based on personality and interests, Yakukon matches people based on their expectations about married life. The site lets users create their own ideal marriage contract and search for compatible partners. Contracts can stipulate anything and everything from childcare and housework, to expected lifestyle and partner income. What is Yakukon Contract? The contract is a detailed document that describes exactly what you can bring to a marriage partnership, and exactly what you expect of your partner. Once done, you search for compatible contracts among other users and other users can search for you. When a user finds a contract they like, they can submit a proposal – a modified (or unmodified) version of their contract – to that user. When users receive a proposal, they can either accept it, reject it, or send a counter offer – an edited version of the proposal they received. Users can go back and forth with counter offers as long as they wish. Once a user accepts a proposal, contact information is exchanged. Then the two users meetup and take things from there. Can I use Yakukon to create a prenuptial agreement? Yes. When you have a successful match on Keiyaku Kekkon, you and your match will have a single unified contract. You can print this out at any time. If you want to make it legally binding, you and your new partner should both modify and sign the final document, ideally with witnesses present. This signed document can then be added to a traditional marriage agreement and approved by your local authorities. Through our system, we hope to make marriage a reality for people frustrated with traditional dating sites.
Industry Groups: Apps, Community and Lifestyle, Internet Services, Media and Entertainment, Mobile, Software

Full Description: Like just about anything, CALOBY was born from necessity and desire.  We are a close knit group that spent many years together in corporate America. Over the years we all struggled with paying the bills, feeding the family, and finding new jobs.  Some of us got a break, while others didn't. So we hope you enjoy the site, community, and products that we offer. Description: W 108 Development LLC is a private property developer.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: W 108 Development LLC is a private property developer in New York that is currently managing the restoration of a historic residential building in the Riverside-West End district of Manhattan. Originally constructed in 1898 by architects Janes & Leo, the property consists of two five-story townhouses on West 108th Street between Broadway and Riverside Drive. Following in the prevalent late 19th century Renaissance Revival style, and with extensive use of terra cotta, brick, and limestone, the architects created a breathtaking front façade of the building. The property renovation currently underway will preserve its 19th century features while showcasing a beautiful, contemporary design for the interior and the rear façade. The renovation will create 11 luxury condominium apartments equipped with high-end kitchens and bathrooms, remote controlled air conditioners, and floor-to-ceiling windows on the rear side of the building. Each unit has its own unique amenity such as a private balcony or private entrance. Residents in this elevator building will also enjoy ample storage space in the basement, as well as community spaces. W 108 Development LLC is investing heavily in the building’s wonderful “hang out” areas where residents will be able to get together and socialize as a community. The “hang out” areas will include a multi-purpose lounge, full kitchen, fitness center, rooftop terrace, and a landscaped backyard.  Finally, we must talk about the location. This culturally-rich Upper West Side neighborhood is filled with excellent restaurants, coffee shops, bars, stores, workout studios, and places of worship. The neighborhood is easily accessible by subway and bus, and is situated near places of interest such as Columbia University, Riverside Park, Central Park, and the famous St. John The Divine Cathedral. All of these attributes combine to make this neighborhood a truly remarkable location.  When you combine the breathtaking front façade, high-end condo units, unprecedented amenities, and fantastic location, you can see why this is truly a one-of-a-kind development.

Headquarters Regions: Greater Denver Area, Western US
Full Description: SprayTraQ was formed in 2016 to provide professional service solutions to transportation providers of perishable food goods for consumption in the US. The company uses a purpose-formulated sanitization and disinfection chemistry formulated to meet the requirements mandated for Sanitary Transportation worldwide. This chemistry and process is applicable to all modes of commercial transportation and containerization. In addition to sanitization, SprayTraQ will provide the required tracking and reporting systems facilitating its customers to be audit-ready in order to meet the new FDA Food Safety Modernization Act requirements.  ‘SprayTraQ’ is the process encompassing: a) the sanitization product, b) the spray application process, and c) Tracking and Auditing Service. The focus of SprayTraQ is to provide sanitization technology including training, implementation, tracking, and reporting capabilities to the extensive US transportation industry and to all foreign food companies exporting into the US. These companies comprise Shippers, Loaders, Carriers, and Receivers and are required by US law to begin implementation by September 2016. Full enforcement began in April 2017.

Description: Bankruptcy lawyer Chicago, bankruptcy in Chicago, Bankruptcy Attorney Chicago, Bankruptcy Service
Headquarters Regions: Greater Chicago Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Address 177 W Washington Street, Chicago, IL 60606 Creditors who are subjected to a bankruptcy case are entitled to their share (according to their due priority) of any distribution that may exist. Further, creditors are entitled to have their day in court, and are allowed to object to the debtor’s plan of reorganization in Chapter 13, 11, 12, and 13, and creditors can object to discharge of debt in Chapter 7 and even have their debt deemed nondischargeable in Chapter 7 in certain circumstances. So, what should a creditor know when they are served with a notice of bankruptcy filing? Initially, cease all telephone calls, billings or law suits that may be pending against the debtor, such actions could be violations of the automatic stay, and subject a creditor to sanctions for actual damages, punitive damages, and even attorneys’ fees of the debtor. After ceasing such conduct, we recommend seeking the advice of an attorney for your particular needs. However, generally, a creditor has the right to file a proof of claim (here is a link to the Northern District of Illinois Proof of Claim Form). If choosing to act without an attorney, please be advised that there are strict deadlines for filing a proof of claim, and the courts generally strictly enforce these deadlines. Further, a creditor must consider if his debt is the type of debt that is not dischargeable in bankruptcy. The most common types of debts that are not dischargeable in bankruptcy are debts arising out of fraudulent, willfully malicious acts by debtor, acts arising out of criminal conduct, and acts arising out of domestic issues (this is not an inclusive list, please contact an attorney to determine if your specific debt may be nondischargeable in bankruptcy). Finally, whether you choose to contact an attorney or not, please feel free to contact the trustee for your particular needs if you suspect that the debtor is not being completely honest in his assets or debts. Creditor vigilance is the best deterrent to bankruptcy abuse.
